Kuhn, a [[running back]], signed with the Steelers as an undrafted free agent following the 2005 draft but was released prior to the beginning of the 2005 season. He signed a contract to play for the [[San Jose SaberCats]] of the [[Arena Football League]] but chose not to report after being signed to the Steelers practice squad on November 30, 2005. Kuhn was on the practice squad roster for the entirety of the Steelers playoff run and their win in [[Super Bowl XL]].
